Features
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph>This sample shows the RelationKind.ForeignKeyReference relation achieved between two tables via a grouping engine.</Paragraph>

<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" >
Interactive Features
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph>Sets up a relation between two tables using a foreign key. ForeignKeyKeyWords is a unique relation kind which, is offered by the grouping engine. It is a foreign key relation where matching keys in the columns of the parent and child table define a relationship between the two tables. This is an m:n relation. Field summaries of the related child table can be referenced using a dot in the FieldDescriptor.MappingName of the main table. This relation kind allows you to have multi-valued columns. All the relation will be get through a DOS window.</Paragraph>



